<subSubSection id="33BD6513FFDB096891EAFC7914CEFAC0" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7B183698FFDB096891EAFC79105EFB35" blockId="1.[151,1436,989,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096891EAFC791518FC15" bold="true" box="[151,271,989,1015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB09689063FC7915D6FC14" authorityName="Painter. Painter" authorityYear="1933" box="[286,449,989,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Neodischistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB09689063FC7915D6FC14" box="[286,449,989,1014]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Neodischistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB0968926AFC79178AFC15" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[791,925,989,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Bombyliini">Bombyliini</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a patch of silvery scales on each side of the face, occiput and abdomen (except for 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB09689214FBA617FDFBF9" box="[873,1002,1026,1052]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Neodischistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB09689214FBA6176BFBF9" box="[873,892,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096892F0FBA617FDFBF9" box="[909,1002,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where males lack silver scales and females have them only on face) and also by the subapical stylus (arista) placed in a dorsal groove of the flagellum (third antennal segment). The slightly sinuous posterior margin of the eye suggests a closer relation with 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB096891A5FBD715D1FB6E" authority="Yeates" authorityName="Yeates" authorityYear="2008" box="[216,454,1138,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Apiformyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096891A5FBD71572FB6E" box="[216,357,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Apiformyia</emphasis>
Yeates
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB096890A9FBD716E9FB6E" authority="Macquart" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1848" box="[468,766,1138,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Heterostylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096890A9FBD7166AFB6E" box="[468,637,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Heterostylum</emphasis>
Macquart
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB0968923DFBD71047FB6E" authority="Edwards" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1937" box="[832,1104,1138,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB0968923DFBD717C2FB6E" box="[832,981,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Triploechus</emphasis>
Edwards
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB096895EDFBD71128FB6E" authorityName="Painter. Painter" authorityYear="1933" box="[1168,1343,1139,1164]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Neodischistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096895EDFBD71128FB6E" box="[1168,1343,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Neodischistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from them, not only by the subapical stylus, but also for the different size of the male ommatidia, which are larger on the upper half of the eye than in the inferior half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B183698FFDB096891EAFB4614CEFAC0" blockId="1.[151,1436,989,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB096891EAFB4614C4FB1E" bold="true" box="[151,211,1250,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Note</emphasis>
. Complete description of 
<taxonomicName id="BCA74D1BFFDB09689369FB4716AAFB1E" authorityName="Painter. Painter" authorityYear="1933" box="[532,701,1251,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Neodischistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49D3EA8AFFDB09689369FB4716AAFB1E" box="[532,701,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="49">Neodischistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="1F364B69FFDB096892DFFB461042FB1E" author="Painter, R. H." box="[930,1109,1250,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref5053" refString="Painter, R. H. (1933) Notes on some Bombyliidae from Panama. American Museum Novitates, 642, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1933">Painter (1933)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1F364B69FFDB0968951EFB461136FB1E" author="Marston, N." box="[1123,1313,1250,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref4925" refString="Marston, N. (1961) Additional notes on the two know species of the genus Neodischistus, Painter (Diptera, Bombyliidae). Boletim da Universidade do Parana. Conselho de Pesquisas, 7, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1961">Marston (1961)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1F364B69FFDB09689422FB4614C2FAC0" author="Hull, F. M." pageId="1" pageNumber="49" pagination="3 - 687" refId="ref4888" refString="Hull, F. M. (1973) The Bee Flies of the World. The genera of the family Bombyliidae. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 286, 3 - 687." type="journal article" year="1973">Hull, 1973</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
